cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the implementation of a hybrid IP/SDN networking solution and advanced services like pseudo wires and virtual switches. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper proposes a system architecture for the OSHI solution. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper may discuss security considerations in the implementation of the hybrid IP/SDN networking solution. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper describes the implementation of management tools for the emulation of the proposed solution using either the Mininet emulator or distributed physical testbeds. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a less likely category, but the paper may discuss information theory concepts related to the performance evaluation of the deployed nodes.
